live preview - https://outpro-oayz.vercel.app/

For Admin page:

Go to mongodb.com/atlas → your cluster → Browse Collections
You'll see your outpro database → click the users collection
If it's empty, first register a normal account on your live site (go to your-frontend.vercel.app/register)
Come back to Atlas → refresh the users collection → you'll see your user document
Click the pencil/edit icon on that document
Find the role field — it says "user"
Change it to "admin"
Click Update

Setup the Backen:

bashcd server
npm install
Create a .env file inside the server folder:
MONGO_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/outpro
JWT_SECRET=anylongrandomstring123456
CLIENT_URL=http://localhost:5173
ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@outpro.in
ADMIN_PASSWORD=Admin@2025
PORT=5000
Start the backend:
bashnpm run dev

Setup the Frontend:

bashcd client
npm install
Create a .env file inside the client folder:
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000
Start the frontend:
bashnpm run dev
Frontend runs on: http://localhost:5173
